&gt;Mantling up onto the hump in the deck was always a chore, underneath your footing sat the chin turret, almost entirely self contained at this point.
&gt;From there it was up onto the ladder that took you up into the pilot&#039;s compartment. Although the squeeze wasn&#039;t particularly narrow, both side of the passageway up were hemmed in by more of the aircraft&#039;s structure, onboard space came at a premium.
