&gt;You glance quickly at the altimeter, now ticking down in a less expedient manner.
&quot;Uhh, seven-fifty.&quot;
&gt;&quot;Good, good. Keep it steady.&quot;
&gt;At this lazy speed you feel more like you&#039;re riding a softly deflating cushion before it starts nudging off from the straightaway.
