&gt;&quot;Final approach, putting down our flaps.&quot;
&gt;The deep whine of hydraulics precedes a slouching pull rearwards as the airbrakes bite into the wind to slow you down.
&gt;But soon that pull starts getting squirrely.
&gt;The yoke jitters as you feel the plane gliding more strongly towards the left.
&gt;Putting your weight in you pull the stick back towards the right.
&gt;&quot;There&#039;s that crosswind again. Don&#039;t over correct, just keep us steady...&quot;
&gt;You aren&#039;t certain exactly how one could over correct in a glide, but you ease off your efforts to shunt the stick to the right and let the eagle shoulder the burden again.
&gt;You keep gazing out at the field, steadily starting to close in as you nervously eye the surrounding trees.
&gt;The whole thing is eerily quiet as the wounded giant of your plane settles towards the ground.
&gt;&quot;Altitude?&quot;
&quot;Three hundred.&quot;
