&gt;That farmhouse watching the field squats in the corner near what looks like a loose dirt road that hugs the treeline. Grain silos flaked apart by rust stand as simplistic imitations of the forest surrounding everything, and a decrepit barn sags to one side as the square slot in the loft gazes over the field.
&gt;If ever there was a place to put a machinegun nest, or whatever the Marauder equivalent is.
